acceptance_criteria: "Every pm item status and metadata surface is reviewed through live CLI inventory; CLI and SDK architecture, quality, security, performance, agent UX, organization, tests, docs, skills, dependencies, bundled packages, installed package state, and all 18 active external package repositories are assessed; every finding is checked against all pm statuses; canonical items receive evidence; only non-duplicate gaps get focused items with complete metadata; no product implementation is performed; tracker health/history/duplicates are verified; tracker-only changes are committed and pushed directly to main."
parent: pm-doxj
risk: low
confidence: high
resolution: "Completed a tracker-only review pass, enriched canonical roadmap items, backfilled active metadata, and filed exactly three deduplicated focused gaps without implementing product changes."
expected_result: "A complete live CLI, SDK, repository, performance, security, quality, package-lifecycle, and 18-repository ecosystem audit documented through pm, with canonical ownership, runnable evidence, no duplicate roadmap growth, and direct-main publication."
actual_result: "All requested surfaces were audited and documented; twenty descriptions and seventeen tag sets were backfilled; pm-2tan, pm-ld0z, and pm-nf7q were created; broad findings were routed to existing owners; final tracker-context linked run passed 8 of 8 checks; no product files changed."
