comments[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-15T19:57:37.772Z",codex-audit-20260715,"Duplicate-check evidence: searched all statuses for ecosystem audit, SDK architecture, simplification, performance, security, external-package, test-organization, renderer-scoping, and plan-help terms; reviewed prior closed audit lineages plus live review pass 90 notes. No active audit execution item represented this new manual pass, so this short-lived Plan is the evidence container; implementation findings remain or are filed under their canonical capability parents."
  "2026-07-15T20:09:05.506Z",codex-audit-20260715,"Completion evidence: linked verification passed for build, typecheck, ESLint, jscpd zero-clone scan, security scan, docs/skills gate, health, and validate. Final health is ok with zero warnings; validation is ok with the known 276 historical resolution metadata warnings; open exact/fuzzy/parent-scope dedupe audits are empty; 225 open items have descriptions and tags; all linked files/docs resolve; git diff --check passes. No issue implementation, product code, test, public doc, or skill content was changed."
  "2026-07-15T20:14:00.807Z",codex-audit-20260715,"Evidence correction: the initial default-context aggregate linked run is visibly retained as 6 passed / 2 failed and must not be read as green. After inspecting the live run record, the complete suite was rerun with explicit tracker context and context preflight; the final run passed 8/8 with zero failures, zero skips, and zero PM context mismatches. Separate tracker-context health and validate reruns also passed. Terminal resolution, expected_result, and actual_result metadata are now populated so this audit does not add to historical close-metadata debt."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-15T20:06:37.689Z",codex-audit-20260715,"Roadmap sequence: SDK and package-boundary primitives; SDK folder and oversized-file decomposition with compatibility tests; help/context projection unification; persistent derived indexes and measured latency budgets; then external package trust tiers and dependency-range convergence. Each slice must preserve feature parity and record before/after latency plus output-byte evidence."
learnings[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-15T20:06:38.577Z",codex-audit-20260715,"All-status metadata review prevented duplicate architecture, performance, strictness, dependency, and package-trust items; only three focused gaps remained. Future ecosystem passes should treat terminal items and recent audit comments as lineage, then prefer enriching canonical work over adding new umbrellas."
  "2026-07-15T20:06:39.347Z",codex-audit-20260715,"Agent-oriented help must model positional actions as first-class discoverable contracts. A command can execute successfully and still block agents when nested help, JSON contracts, and completion disagree about its shape."
  "2026-07-15T20:06:40.190Z",codex-audit-20260715,"Package collision diagnostics need semantic ownership, not only hook-name equality. A renderer that returns null outside a marker-scoped payload composes differently from an unconditional global renderer and should be represented explicitly in the SDK contract."
