  "Final tracker audit is healthy: health has zero warnings; validation is ok with only the known 276 historical resolution-metadata warnings; exact, fuzzy, and parent-scope open duplicate audits each return zero clusters; all 225 open items have descriptions and tags; the living roadmap milestone is the sole intentional root; normalization proposes no mutations.",pm health; pm validate; pm dedupe-audit in three modes; pm normalize --dry-run; pm list --status open --full,"No new health, history, duplicate, metadata, lineage, or normalization defect"
  "Every file and documentation link on pm-45lr, pm-2tan, pm-ld0z, and pm-nf7q resolves in the repository. git diff --check passes and no product source, test, documentation, or skill file was changed.",pm files and pm docs --validate-paths for four items; git diff --check; git status --short,All linked paths exist and the diff is tracker/planning evidence only
  "Correction to the earlier aggregate-run wording: the first default schema-context run recorded 6 passed and 2 failed, so it is retained as diagnostic history and is not the final passing proof. A full rerun with explicit tracker context and context preflight passed all 8 of 8 linked commands with zero failures and zero context mismatches.",pm test pm-45lr --run --pm-context tracker --override-linked-pm-context --check-context --progress,"8 passed, 0 failed, 0 skipped; two tracker-read commands have matching source and sandbox item counts"
plan_decisions[1]{ts,author,decision,rationale,evidence}:
  "2026-07-15T20:05:29.103Z",codex-audit-20260715,Preserve the existing capability roadmap and add only three focused gaps.,"All-status searches and full live metadata showed the structural SDK, performance, strictness, dependency, package-trust, duplication, and simplification findings already have canonical ownership. Creating parallel epics would fragment context and violate duplicate-safe planning.","Reused pm-801d, pm-kb5h, pm-onpb, pm-tll8, pm-o8um, pm-quzx, pm-usfg, pm-n7rr, pm-92if, and pm-doxj; created only pm-2tan, pm-ld0z, and pm-nf7q."
plan_discoveries[7]{ts,author,text}:
  "2026-07-15T20:05:24.157Z",codex-audit-20260715,"Live inventory found 1842 items: 1608 closed, 222 open, and 12 canceled; 1850 history streams and 29511 events; zero lock, integrity, history-drift, semantic-staleness, exact-title-duplicate, fuzzy-duplicate, or normalization findings. The only systematic metadata gap was 20 open descriptions and 17 open tag sets, now backfilled through pm."
  "2026-07-15T20:05:24.814Z",codex-audit-20260715,"The SDK remains dense at 70 source files and roughly 52k raw lines, with 46 files at src/sdk root; canonical pm-kb5h already owns the topology migration. Largest implementation units remain 3.4k-4.0k lines and are already owned by pm-yh8r, pm-kb5h, and pm-usfg. Eight test suites are 3.3k-7.3k lines and lacked a focused intra-file decomposition ratchet, now captured by pm-ld0z."
  "2026-07-15T20:05:25.460Z",codex-audit-20260715,"Fresh local quality evidence passed build, typecheck, ESLint, duplicate-code detection across 621 files and 357795 lines with zero clones, security scan, docs/skills quality, static quality, and package boundary checks. pnpm audit found zero advisories across 330 dependencies. Strict TypeScript is active but noUncheckedIndexedAccess, exactOptionalPropertyTypes, and noImplicitOverride remain disabled under canonical pm-onpb."
  "2026-07-15T20:05:26.124Z",codex-audit-20260715,"Three-run local CLI timing showed version 56.8-71.5ms, get 484.7-1091ms, list-open 727-993ms, context 949-987ms, search 803-898ms, and next 913-1663ms. TOON reduced context output from 6141 to 4255 bytes and list-open from 5213 to 3950 bytes versus JSON. Existing pm-801d owns the persistent derived-index solution; this pass adds fresh jitter evidence only."
  "2026-07-15T20:05:26.776Z",codex-audit-20260715,"All 18 active public external pm repositories were checked against live source manifests and npm latest metadata. Versions align, every package declares Node 22.18 or newer, and the release/audit/pack/test/check baseline is broadly consistent. Canonical pm-o8um and pm-quzx own the remaining trust-tier, dependency-range, parity, and duplicate-package policy."
  "2026-07-15T20:05:27.486Z",codex-audit-20260715,"Isolated deep package doctor is non-blocking but reports two renderer override warnings for pm-changelog JSON and TOON renderers. The callbacks are marker-scoped and return null outside their payload, so permanent warning state does not distinguish safe scoped composition from an actual global replacement. New focused issue pm-nf7q owns this contract gap."
  "2026-07-15T20:05:28.316Z",codex-audit-20260715,"Agent help has a positional-action blind spot: pm plan advertises create as an action and the command executes, but pm plan create --help --json is rejected as unknown_command while the help model reports no subcommands. New focused issue pm-2tan owns unified positional-action help, contracts, and completion discoverability."
