  plan-step-002,2,"Audit CLI and SDK architecture, folder density, large files, type safety, dead/duplicate code, dependencies, security, performance, UX, docs, tests, and skills",completed,"2026-07-15T19:57:25.915Z","2026-07-15T20:05:30.441Z","Completed manual CLI/SDK architecture, source/test size, type safety, dependency, security, duplicate, performance, output-efficiency, docs, skills, and repository organization review with fresh local gates.","2026-07-15T20:05:30.441Z"
  plan-step-003,3,"Audit bundled, installed, global, and all active external pm packages against SDK and lifecycle contracts",completed,"2026-07-15T19:57:25.915Z","2026-07-15T20:05:31.139Z","Completed bundled, installed, global, catalog, lifecycle, isolated-doctor, and live 18-repository external package review against source and npm metadata.","2026-07-15T20:05:31.139Z"
  plan-step-004,4,Deduplicate every finding across all statuses and enrich canonical roadmap items,completed,"2026-07-15T19:57:25.915Z","2026-07-15T20:05:31.787Z",Every finding was searched across all statuses and routed to canonical owners. Twenty description gaps and seventeen tag gaps were filled on existing open items without changing their scope.,"2026-07-15T20:05:31.787Z"
  plan-step-005,5,"Create only missing focused work items with evidence, acceptance criteria, relationships, and execution guidance",completed,"2026-07-15T19:57:25.915Z","2026-07-15T20:05:32.558Z","Created only pm-2tan for positional plan-help discovery, pm-ld0z for giant test-suite decomposition, and pm-nf7q for scoped renderer doctor semantics; each has full metadata, relations, files, docs, tests, and duplicate-check evidence.","2026-07-15T20:05:32.558Z"
  plan-step-006,6,Validate the final tracker-only state and publish it directly to main,completed,"2026-07-15T19:57:25.915Z","2026-07-15T20:09:06.336Z","Validated all linked gates, tracker health/history/duplicates/metadata, link existence, and diff hygiene. The resulting tracker-only plan and findings are ready for the requested direct-main commit and push.","2026-07-15T20:09:06.336Z"
body: "AUDIT OUTCOME\n\nThe project management system is structurally healthy and already expresses the philosophy project management equals context management through full metadata, history, graph, contracts, packages, context views, and agent-oriented TOON output. This pass found no security advisory, integrity drift, exact or fuzzy active duplicate cluster, normalization requirement, exact duplicate code clone, or exact duplicate Markdown or skill body.\n\nThe primary optimization direction remains simplification through one SDK-backed source of truth: thin CLI adapters, public SDK primitives, runtime contracts, capability-scoped packages, persistent derived indexes, compact projected output, and explicit compatibility policy. Existing roadmap owners cover that direction and should be executed in dependency order rather than replaced by another umbrella.\n\nNewly isolated work is intentionally narrow:\n1. pm-2tan makes positional plan actions discoverable through the same help, JSON contract, and completion surfaces as ordinary subcommands.\n2. pm-ld0z splits the largest 3.3k-7.3k-line test files by behavioral boundary and introduces a maintainability ratchet without reducing coverage.\n3. pm-nf7q lets package doctor distinguish globally replacing renderers from marker-scoped composable renderers, retaining collision safety without permanent false-positive warnings.\n\nExecution guidance: complete shared SDK and package-boundary primitives first; then folder and file decomposition; then help and context projection unification; then persistent read indexes and latency budgets; then external-package trust tiers and dependency policy. Preserve every public feature, require compatibility tests for moves, and measure user-visible output bytes and warm/cold latency before and after each slice."
